data.meta_description:
Duane Carter passed away in Millinocket, Maine. This is the full obituary story where you can share condolences and memories. Published in the Bangor Daily News.

<meta name=
data.text:
Millinocket - Duane A. Carter, 84, died Tuesday, November 13, 2018, at a Millinocket hospital. He was born to March 13, 1934, in Millinocket, the son of Albert and Ethelyn Mae (Morris) Carter.

Duane worked in the financial services sector for his entire working career, spending 10 years with the Millinocket Trust Company, 19 years with the Michigan National Bank in Detroit, Michigan, and 10 years with the Barnett Bank in Clearwater, Florida. After retiring home to Millinocket, Duane served 1 term on the Millinocket Housing Authority.

He is survived by a sister, Mary Griffin of Presque Isle; a brother, Paul Carter and his wife, Maryann, of Millinocket; a stepson, Wayne Jewell and his wife, Karen; a stepdaughter, Nadine Corey; and stepgrandchildren, Megan, Daniel, Jason, and Monica Jewell, and Ronald Corey; a brother-in-law, Warren S. Meyer and his wife, Jackie; and several nieces, nephews, and cousins. In addition to his parents, Duane was predeceased by his wife, Louise A. Carter; a sister, Edwina "Sis" Caron; and two brothers, Melvin Carter and Dudley Carter.

Friends are invited to visit with the family 1-2 p.m. Saturday, November 17, at the Lamson Funeral Home, 11 Tamarack Street, Millinocket. Graveside services will be held in the springtime at Millinocket Cemetery. Messages of condolence may be expressed at .

Published on November 14, 2018
